---
import ArticleLayout from '@/layouts/ArticleLayout.astro';
---
<ArticleLayout
  title="BBQ It — What to Buy First (Purchase Priority)"
  description="BBQ It purchase priority guide. Know exactly what to buy first, second, and third for the fastest progression at every stage."
  quickAnswer="Buy in this order: Standard Grill → Metal Table → Quick Hands → Seasoned Chef → Auto Sell → Offline Grill → Offline Storage. This maximizes your income growth at every stage."
  faq={[
    { question: 'What is the first thing I should buy in BBQ It?', answer: 'The Standard Grill (500 cash) for an extra cooking slot, immediately followed by the Metal Table (800 cash) for double customer capacity. These two purchases have the fastest ROI.' },
    { question: 'When should I buy offline grills?', answer: 'Buy your first Offline Grill after you have Auto Sell (4,000 cash) and at least a Pro Grill. Offline grills are a mid-game investment that pays off over time.' },
    { question: 'Should I save up for expensive upgrades or buy cheaper ones first?', answer: 'Almost always buy cheaper upgrades first. Multiple small upgrades compound faster than one big purchase. Use our Upgrade ROI Calculator to compare.' },
  ]}
  relatedGuides={[
    { title: 'Upgrades Guide', url: '/upgrades/', description: 'All upgrades ranked.' },
    { title: 'Money Guide', url: '/money-guide/', description: 'How to earn money fast.' },
    { title: 'Upgrade ROI Calculator', url: '/calculator/upgrade-roi/', description: 'Find the best upgrade.' },
    { title: 'Beginner Guide', url: '/beginner-guide/', description: 'Getting started guide.' },
  ]}
>
  <h2 class="text-2xl font-bold mb-4">Early Game Priority (0-2K cash)</h2>
  <ol class="list-decimal list-inside space-y-2 text-gray-600 dark:text-gray-400 mb-8">
    <li><strong>Standard Grill</strong> (500) — More slots = more meat cooking = more money.</li>
    <li><strong>Metal Table</strong> (800) — Double your customers, double your income.</li>
    <li><strong>Quick Hands</strong> (500) — 10% faster cooking adds up fast.</li>
  </ol>

  <h2 class="text-2xl font-bold mb-4">Mid Game Priority (2K-10K cash)</h2>
  <ol class="list-decimal list-inside space-y-2 text-gray-600 dark:text-gray-400 mb-8">
    <li><strong>Seasoned Chef</strong> (1,000) — Perfect cooks are worth 50-75% more.</li>
    <li><strong>Rapid Flip</strong> (2,000) — Stack cook speed for faster throughput.</li>
    <li><strong>Pro Grill</strong> (2,000) — 4 slots + 10% speed.</li>
    <li><strong>Auto Sell</strong> (4,000) — Frees you up to focus on cooking.</li>
    <li><strong>Offline Grill (Basic)</strong> (3,000) — Start passive income.</li>
    <li><strong>Offline Storage</strong> (3,000) — Don't lose offline earnings to the cap.</li>
  </ol>

  <h2 class="text-2xl font-bold mb-4">Late Game Priority (10K+ cash)</h2>
  <ol class="list-decimal list-inside space-y-2 text-gray-600 dark:text-gray-400 mb-8">
    <li><strong>Premium Table</strong> (3,000) — 3 customers + 10% offer boost.</li>
    <li><strong>Master Chef</strong> (5,000) — +30% perfect cook chance.</li>
    <li><strong>Elite Grill</strong> (8,000) — 5 slots + 20% speed.</li>
    <li><strong>Heavy Hitter</strong> (7,000) — +20% meat weight for premium meats.</li>
    <li><strong>Blaze Cook</strong> (8,000) — Max cook speed.</li>
    <li><strong>Offline Efficiency</strong> (6,000) — 25% faster offline cooking.</li>
    <li><strong>BBQ Legend</strong> (15,000) — Max quality upgrade.</li>
    <li><strong>Golden Table</strong> (12,000) — Best table in the game.</li>
  </ol>
</ArticleLayout>
